msContents.summary: A manual of judicial procedures and municipal law of the town of Olmütz (Czech, Olomouc). The manual is divided into 33 articles, and two parts, with the second part (apparently that pertaining to municipal law as opposed to court procedures) beginning at article 14 (f. 30r). It has a table of contents (f. 94r-100v). Remnants of a red wax seal that was removed are visible on f. 1r.
msContents.textLang: German, with some passages or citations in Latin (f. 1v-2r, 3v, 4r-4v, 6r, 11v, 13v, 48r, 61v, 62r, 68v, 71r, 71v, 72r, 74v), as well as Latin terms scattered throughout

msItem.title: Der Stadt Olmütz Gerichts Proces undt Stadt Rechtenn

supportDesc.extent: 104 leaves : 199 x 151 (160 x 120) mm. bound to 199 x 155 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, iii + 100 + i; 1-93, [94-100]; contemporary foliation in ink, modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto (some numbers partially trimmed).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a German cursive hand.

binding.p: Contemporary blind-stamped pigskin (Zacour-Hirsch), with remnants of two clasps.

origin.p: Written in Olomouc (Czech Republic) in the 17th century (Zacour-Hirsch).

history.provenance: Sold by Mr. Tallandier (Marseille), 1942, and formerly part of a private library that was sold in Monte Carlo earlier that year (note, inside upper cover).
